 <body>
  <p>The editor allows you to personalize an email or landing page by inserting links into the HTML content elements.</p> 
  <p>You can insert a link into any page element: image, word, group of words, block of text, etc.</p> 
  <note>
   <p> The images below show how to insert a link using the <a href="../../designing/using/about-email-content-design.md#using-the-creative-designer">Creative Designer</a>. </p> 
  </note>
  <ol>
   <li><p>Select an element and click <strong>Insert link</strong> from the toolbar.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/des_insert_link.png" title="" /></li>
   <li><p>Choose the type of link you want to create:</p> 
    <ul>
     <li><p><strong>Link to an external URL</strong>: allows you to add a link to a URL.</p> <p>You can define personalization for your URLs. See <a href="../../designing/using/personalizing-urls.md" target="_blank">Personalizing URLs</a>.</p> </li>
     <li><p><strong>Link that defines an action</strong>: allows you to define an action when an element in the landing page is clicked.</p> 
      <note>
       <p> This type of link is only available for landing pages. </p> 
      </note></li>
     <li><p><strong>Link to a landing page</strong>: allows you to access an Adobe Campaign landing page.</p> </li>
     <li><p><strong>Subscription link</strong>: allows you to insert a link to subscribe to an Adobe Campaign service.</p> </li>
     <li><p><strong>Unsubscription link</strong>: allows you to insert a link to unsubscribe from an Adobe Campaign service.</p> </li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><p>Modify the link parameters as needed:</p> 
    <ul>
     <li><p>You can modify the text displayed to the profile.</p> </li>
     <li><p>You can edit the link type: URL, action, landing page, or service.</p> </li>
     <li><p>You can set the browser behavior when the user clicks the link (for example, open a new window).</p> 
      <note>
       <p> Defining the browser behavior only apply to landing pages. </p> 
      </note></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><p>Validate the link creation.</p> </li>
  </ol>
  <p>Once the link is created, you can still modify it by selecting it and re-opening the link popup or by editing the link target directly in the settings of the element displayed in the left panel.</p> 
  <p>When editing an email with the <a href="../../designing/using/about-email-content-design.md#using-the-creative-designer">Creative Designer</a>, you can easily access and modify the links that you created from the table listing all the URLs included in the email. This list enables you to have a centralized view and to locate each URL in the email content. To access it, see <a href="../../designing/using/about-tracked-urls.md" target="_blank">About tracked URLs</a>.</p> 
  <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/des_link_list.png" title="" />
  <note>
   <p> Personalized URLs such as <strong>Mirror page URL</strong> or <strong>Unsubscription</strong> link cannot be modified from this list. All other links are editable. </p> 
  </note>
  <p></p> 
